    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a high-variance slate today, anchored by **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, who earns our strongest play of the day with a 73.83 efficiency score. Despite the potential for a #9 batting order slot, the combination of a porous 5.43 xERA from Randy V\u00e1squez and an elite dynamic platoon advantage makes **Pete Crow-Armstrong** a critical engine for our stolen base production. **Hyeseong Kim** follows as a strong secondary option (61.59); he benefits from a favorable matchup against Chris Paddack and wind conditions that amplify his scoring ceiling. While **Junior Caminero** faces a tougher test against the 3.43 xERA of Parker Messick, his #2 spot in the order provides enough volume-based security to merit a start, even with the dynamic platoon disadvantage.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Josh Smith**, who sits at a marginal 33.64 score. While we weigh SB potential heavily, **Josh Smith** is stifled by a difficult matchup against Max Fried and an \"elite hold\" factor from the opposition that significantly dampens his stolen base upside. Consequently, we are keeping **Josh Smith** benched to preserve our limited game caps for more favorable conditions. We must also continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, who remains on the IL, and ensure that our lineup adjustments account for the absence of **Yordan Alvarez** and **Kyle Schwarber**, both of whom are unavailable today due to team off-days. \n\nWe are tracking several risks as we await official lineups: **Chase Meidroth**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, and **Luke Raley** are all currently projected based on assumed order placement. **Chase Meidroth** is of particular note, as a negative wind impact (-9%) tempers his efficiency against Jack Kochanowicz, and any slide out of the leadoff spot would immediately threaten his 51.90 score. Furthermore, while **Luke Raley** offers solid upside, the L/L platoon disadvantage against Connor Prielipp keeps him in the lower tier of our starts; we will be watching for any late-breaking news that might trigger a swap with our available bench depth.",
